node.title: Turquoise
node.description: One from the archives--After one of the worst summer storms I've seen, the skies cleared just before sunset.

node.title: CRV Rocks
node.description: Potholes at the Cherokee Rock Village near Collinsville, AL.

node.title: Winter at High Falls
node.description: Taken in between snow and sleet showers this past weekend.  As you can see on the natural bridge and ice covered grass, it was a cold day.

node.title: Balanced
node.description: Tripod balancing act above some little cascades in the Talladega National Forest.  Just had to get a close-up of this moss covered rock....

node.title: Up Close and Personal
node.description: This is a small cascade just below Branch Falls after heavy rain.  I had to work for this one, shooting in waist deep, fast moving water.  Thankfully there were no casualties.

node.title: Hopeful
node.description: Downstream view from Branch Falls, also known by some as "hopeful falls."  Typically there is very little water here, but a nice place to come after heavy winter rains.  Strangely this shot has an HDR quality to it, but it is one single exposure.  Not sure why it turned out this way, but am pleased with the colors that came through.

node.title: Somewhere below Turkey Foot...
node.description: Lower falls below Turkey Foot Falls in the Bankhead National Forest.

node.title: Bankhead Highway
node.description: Travelling through the Bankhead National Forest is sometimes done more easily at creek level than along the trails and ridges. I dont have a description for this spot, other than being a creek below Turkey Foot Falls.
